        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/25785",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "ML post and IRC discussion regarding this issue:\n\nhttp:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Validating-SSL-server-certs---using-CA-certs-p20225319.html\nhttp:\/\/zftalk.com\/logs\/view\/zftalk.dev\/2008\/10\/29\/\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-06T13:03:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-06T13:03:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29608",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with ZF-3616, inclusion of cURL Adapter into trunk, released in 1.8",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beberlei",
                        "name": "beberlei",
                        "displayName": "Benjamin Eberlei",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-20T03:46:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-20T03:46:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/29612",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is great news! I've been using your adapter for a while, the fact that it will be provided with ZF will however make things easier ;-)\n\nAnyways, this doesn't solve the issue for me: Zend_Http_Client is still to be considered insecure with HTTPS and still prone to MITM attacks. This is also true for all Service-Components based on Zend_Http_Clients. The fact that there finally IS a secure connection adapter does neither fix the default one (Socket), nor does it tell coders to NOT use the default one for HTTPS unless fixed nor does it fix other components based on Zend_Http_Client.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-03-20T04:06:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-03-20T04:06:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32874",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Depends on being able to set context parameters on the stream. Work in progress on that.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-23T14:34:54.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-23T14:34:54.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32876",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Now that the setStreamContext() and getStreamContext() methods have been added (in trunk, CS-17009), you should be able to force peer validation easily. \n\nWe can't set this behavior to be the default one, because of BC issues. I also suspect most people will not want this because it makes development and testing harder.\n\nThanks for reporting!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-23T14:45:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-23T14:45:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32896",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "That's great news, thank you!\n\nLet me add some thoughts regarding default settings. First, this is what\nI posted last autumn to ZF's mailinglist:\n\n> Unfortunately switching validation on per default is not an option as\n> it would break currently working applications. I would suggest to change\n> this with ZF 2.0 - as other libs \/ languages I know (CURL, Java, C# etc)\n> are doing so out of the box. And in my believes this is the only correct\n> way of using HTTPS. If someone wants to do insecure things he is free to\n> do so, but he has to explicitly switch checks off.\n\n(see http:\/\/www.nabble.com\/Validating-SSL-server-certs---using-CA-certs-p20225319.html for full post)\n\nI don't know which Zend_Service_Whatever-Classes are based on HTTPS\n(a quick grep showed Amazon_Ec2, Delicious, ReCaptcha), probably all of\nthem are using Zend_Http_Client - with insecure defaults. And I'm pretty\nsure others will follow.\n\nTherefore I strongly suggest changing default settings with ZF 2.0. Many\ndevelopers just don't realize that self-signed certificates lead HTTPS ad\nabsurdum - and also not verifying signed ones does. If someone insists on\nusing useless certificates he can do so. But he needs to be made aware of\ndoing something REALLY bad (and shall be forced into explicitely allowing\nthis in his own code).\n\nWhat is the best way to add a note assuring this doesn't will be forgotten?\nOpen a seperate ticket against \"Next Major Release\"?\n\nBest regards,\nThomas Gelf\n\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tgelf",
                        "name": "tgelf",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Gelf",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T02:27:04.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T02:27:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/37462",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Postponing issue until 2.0 when we can change the defaults in the socket adapter to be more like that of the curl adapter: validating all certificates by default.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-06T20:15:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-06T20:15:15.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
